      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOSSY BENITA (1) was well ridden here last time out to win the G3 Mannerism Stakes but put up a solid number there and this doesn't look any harder at all. She's got a bit of weight but should land in front and give a huge sight once more. MERRIGOLD (2) is off a let up for this, last seen chasing home Taken over 1700m. Fancy 1400m is her best trip and she gets in quite well with 54.5kg. TEINE AULELEI (7) got home well fresh in the Inglis Sprint over 1200m, beaten three lengths. This trip will suit better and she's always promised a bit. BETWITCHERY (9) is racing well having won two of her past three. She drops 5kg and can measure up. YUM (8)  ran well fresh behind a good filly in Educated and can improve up in trip.",
